	  	<h1> Your Guide to Colorado Adventure </h1>
      <h5> All Colorado Events and Activities, Any Local Area </h5>
	  	<p>
	  		Looking for fun things to do in Colorado? World class travel adventures abound in the beautiful state of Colorado! Whether you are looking for a family vacation or an action-packed adventure, Colorado activities and events cater to visitors of all ages and abilities.<br><br>

        Colorado boasts 300 days of sun each year. This increases your access to over 7 mountain ranges, 4 National Parks, 7 National Monuments, 11 National Forests, 240 golf courses, 25 ski areas, 60 terrain parks, river rafting, horseback riding and 54 peaks that rise more than 14,000 feet above sea level.<br><br>

        Welcome to Colorado, where you can enjoy your vacation in any way you choose.
	  	</p>

      <h3> <a href='#'>Running: Races, Charity Runs, Obstacle Course & Mud Runs </a></h3>
      <p>
        Colorado boasts one of the Countries most fit populations. It's no wonder running events in Colorado draw big crowds all across our beautiful State. Choose from world class events like the Bolder Boulder, charity 5K's and obstacle & mud runs. There is something for everyone! 
      </p>

      <h3> <a href='#'>Colorado Bicycle Races, Rides and Events </a></h3>
      <p>
        Riding a bicycle is a wonderful and intimate way to experience Colorado! Whether you prefer road biking or trail riding Colorado has plenty of choices from the grasslands of the Eastern Plains to metro trails in our front range cities to challenging rides over mountain passes. Take a look at our list and be sure to plan a ride while you're here.   
      </p>

      <h3> <a href='/horseback'>Horseback Rides </a></h3>
      <p>
        Horseback riding in Colorado is a great way to visit Colorado's back country. Get off the main trail and see streams and waterfalls, fields of wild flowers and majestic views of Colorado's mountains. You can choose from outfitters, stables or state parks to arrange everything from a one hour ride to evening rides complete with steak dinners to overnight trips with tents and campfires.Horseback rides make for great family memories.
      </p>

      <h3> <a href='/winecountry'>Colorado Wine Country </a></h3>
      <p>
        Colorado's Wine Country is centered in Palisade which is just outside Grand Junction in Western Colorado. The Palisade area houses over 20 Wineries. The high altitude and dry climate produce many interesting varieties of wine. Be sure to tour the beautiful vineyards and enjoy the tasting rooms and quality restaurants of the Palisade region. 
      </p>

      <h3> <a href='/stateparks'>Colorado State Parks </a></h3>
      <p>
        Colorado State Parks offer activity and fun as diverse as the geography, climate and scenery of Colorado. With 42 State Parks and over 225,000 acres to explore families and adventurers will be challenged to fit all this activity into one trip. You can do it all; camping, boating, horseback riding, whitewater rafting, sailing, hiking, bike riding, rock climbing and zip lines. Be sure to pack the sunscreen since you'll be spending plenty of time outdoors.
      </p>

      <h3> <a href='/golfcourse'>Golf Courses in Colorado </a></h3>
      <p>
        It's true! Golf balls do fly farther in Colorado. As always the challenge is to hit them straight. Golfing in Colorado challenges players in many ways. Golf's greatest course designers have embraced the scenery and geography of Colorado to design some of the most challenging and beautiful courses in the country. Golfers can easily be distracted by the scenery and wildlife sightings as they play these wonderful golf courses.
      </p>

